# ============================================
# POLICE ROLE HIERARCHY REFERENCE
# ============================================
# 1. CONSTABLE - View only
# 2. HEAD_CONSTABLE - View only
# 3. ASI - View only
# 4. SI - Can create FIR, search, upload evidence
# 5. INSPECTOR - Can create FIR, search, upload evidence
# 6. DSP - Can approve FIR
# 7. SP - Superintendent of Police
# 8. DIG - Deputy Inspector General
# 9. IG - Inspector General
# 10. ADGP - Additional DGP
# 11. DGP - Director General of Police
# 12. ADMIN - System Admin (user management only)
# 4. SI (Sub-Inspector)
# 5. INSPECTOR
# 6. DSP (Deputy Superintendent of Police)
# 7. ASP (Additional Superintendent of Police)
# 8. SP (Superintendent of Police)
# 9. DIG (Deputy Inspector General)
# 10. IG (Inspector General)
# 11. ADGP (Additional Deputy General of Police)
# 12. DGP (Director General of Police)
# 13. ADMIN (System Admin)

# ============================================
# PERMISSION LEVELS
# ============================================
# CONSTABLE - HEAD_CONSTABLE - ASI:
#   - View FIR only
#   - NO search, NO evidence access

# SI - INSPECTOR:
#   - FIR CRUD
#   - Evidence upload & download
#   - Case Retrieval (semantic search)
#   - NO approve

# DSP - SP:
#   - Approve FIRs
#   - View analytics
#   - Evidence access
#   - Case search

# DIG - DGP:
#   - Full access
#   - View all cases
#   - Analytics
#   - Evidence
#   - User management

# ADMIN:
#   - Create users (ANY ROLE)
#   - View admin dashboard
#   - Cannot create FIR
#   - Cannot upload evidence
